text: Le Mesnil-Saint-Jean is a commune in the Eure department in Normandy in northern France. It was established on 1 January 2019 by merger of the former communes of Saint-Georges-du-Mesnil (the seat) and Saint-Jean-de-la- Léqueraye.Arrêté préfectoral 25 September 2018 ==See also== *Communes of the Eure department ==References== Category:Communes of Eure Category:States and territories established in 2019
title: Le Mesnil-Saint-Jean
